OL,3,CPermanent chair appointed to troubled
OL,4,Chealth board
OL,6,FThe appointment of a permanent
OL,7,Fchairman at the troubled Betsi
OL,8,FCadwaladr Health Board has been
OL,9,Fdescribed as a "key" move to making
OL,10,Fimprovements.
OL,12,FThe former leader of Gwynedd Council,
OL,13,FDyfed Edwards will continue in the
OL,14,Frole, eleven months after being
OL,15,Fappointed temporarily.
OL,17,FMr Edwards acknowledged that the
OL,18,Fhealth board has been
OL,19,F"underperforming" and "falling short
OL,20,Fin terms of delivering world-class
OL,21,Fpublic services for our communities".
